<DOC><DOCNO> AP880426-0088 </DOCNO><FILEID>AP-NR-04-26-88 0850EDT</FILEID><FIRST>u i PM-Lebanon-Israel 1stLd-Writethru a0549 04-26 0220</FIRST><SECOND>PM-Lebanon-Israel, 1st Ld-Writethru, a0549,0225</SECOND><HEAD>URGENT</HEAD><HEAD>Two Israelis, Three Guerrilas Die In Clash</HEAD><NOTE>Eds: Combines previous. Adds day in lead.</NOTE><DATELINE>BEIRUT, Lebanon (AP) </DATELINE><TEXT>   Two Israeli soldiers and three Arabguerrillas died today in a predawn clash near the border withIsrael, police reported.   A police spokesman said the clash began at 3:30 a.m. near thesouthern village of Kfar Shouba when Israeli troops opened fire ona seven-man guerrilla group. The spokesman said the guerrillas weremade up of two pro-Soviet groups _ the Lebanese Communist Party andthe Popular Front for the Liberation of Palestine of George Habash.   A ``fierce clash'' raged for about three hours, said the policespokesman, who cannot be named in line with standing regulations.   The Israelis ``fired flares at the rate of 20 every five minutesas their helicopter gunships chased the guerrillas in the region,''he said.   The police spokesman said the guerrillas ``apparently (were)ambushed before launching a cross-border raid into northernIsrael.''   Kfar Chuba is a small village about one mile from the Israeliborder on the slopes of biblical Mt. Hermon that towers over theregion where the borders of Lebanon, Israel and Syria converge.   The village is inside Israel's self-designated ``security zone''that was established when Israel withdrew the bulk of its troopsfrom Lebanon in 1985.</TEXT></DOC>